# Workspace Recipe LLM Guide

## Purpose

Use this command to inspect, validate, preview, and render local recipes. Recipes are the preferred way to create project-shaped scaffolding.

## When To Run

- Before hand-writing a new module shape that may already have a recipe.
- When validating recipe changes.
- When previewing generated files before writing them.

## How To Read The Result

- Listing shows available recipes.
- Summary shows required inputs and planned targets.
- Check validates recipe metadata and sample rendering.
- Dry run shows what would be created or skipped without writing changes.

## Examples

- If a recipe exists for a module shape, inspect it before creating files manually.
- If required inputs are missing, provide them with explicit variables instead of editing rendered output afterward.
- If dry run shows an existing target will be skipped, decide whether to preserve, rename, or edit manually.
- If check fails, fix the recipe before attempting generation.

## Agent Tips

- Prefer a local recipe over inventing scaffolding.
- Inspect a recipe before rendering it.
- Use variables explicitly and keep generated names aligned with the target module.
- Run check or dry run before writing generated files.
